Install tar.gz archive
  Source: https://askubuntu.com/questions/639389/install-tar-gz-but-no-configure-folder-on-install-file
  "To install it, I suggest you to move the folder to /opt/ by running
  
  sudo mv ~/Downloads/RoKiSim/ /opt/                  # to make the program executable by running
  chmod +x /opt/RoKiSim/bin/RoKiSim                   # and to add a symbolic link to /usr/bin/ by running
  sudo ln -s /opt/RoKiSim/bin/RoKiSim /usr/bin/rokisim
  After that, you'll be able to run the program just by running rokisim."

Customized commands
  1. Using alias
  example: alias yt='....'
  2. Using bash function
  example: yt() {
    yt-dlp -f "bv*[ext=mp4]+ba[ext=m4a]/b[ext=mp4]" --merge-output-format mp4 "$@"
  }
  After that, source .bashrc before using the commands. Another option is using the script should the process is complex.

File installation
  1. Move to the tar file to /opt
  2. Make it executable
  chmod +x [file]
  3. Create symbolic link to /usr/bin: sudo ln -s [current file location] [usr/...]
  4. Open terminal and type its name to run the program
  (Source: https://askubuntu.com/questions/639389/install-tar-gz-but-no-configure-folder-on-install-file)
  Nowadays, we can just put the tar file either extract it or drag to the store of your linux distro

