KDE Vietnamese Keyboard
 1. sudo pacman -S fcitx5 fcitx5-gtk fcitx5-qt fcitx5-configtool fcitx5-unikey
 2. nano ~/.xprofile
	export GTK_IM_MODULE=fcitx
	export QT_IM_MODULE=fcitx
	export XMODIFIERS=@im=fcitx
 3. Reboot
 4. Open Settings/Keyboard/Virtual Keyboard
 5. Select either fcitx 5 wayland or fcitx 5
 6. Either left click on the keyboard icon on the left of the taskbar or
	Settings/Input Method (In Language and Time)
 7. Add Input Method, type Vietnamese and select Unikey
 8. Test and add Hotkey for quickswap between languages
 9. Click configure global options (Bottom left of Input Method)
 10. Remove every preconfig hotkeys and add hotkey in Toggle Input Method.
 11. Remember to Apply then test again
