Github cases
Case 1: Change name of the directory in git repo

Because github does not provide means of changing directory name, only in terminal can that happen.
    git mv <old-name> <new-name>
Then the git commit and git push.


Case 2: Naming convention

Use the this-is-the-name for github naming convention.


Case 3: Move multiple files in git repo

    mv dir1/file1 dir1/file2 dir2/
    mv dir/* DIR/


Case 4: Login

Setup username and email:
    git config --global user.name ""
    git config --global user.email ""

Case 5: Create git folder

    git init
    git status
    git add .
    git commit -m "" # make first commit
    git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo-name.git
    git branch -M main
    git push -u origin main


Case 6: Conflict solution

    git pull origin main
OR  git pull origin main --rebase # reconcile history
    git add .
    git rebase --continue
    git push origin main  


Case 7: Check graph

    git log --oneline --all --graph

